Cluster Analysis

library(cluster)
library(GGally)

# Determine k
sil_width <- vector()
for (i in 2:10) {
    pam_fit <- pam(infidelity, diss = TRUE, k = i)
    sil_width[i] <- pam_fit$silinfo$avg.width
}

ggplot() + geom_line(aes(x = 1:10, y = sil_width)) + scale_x_continuous(name = "k", 
    breaks = 1:10)

# PAM

Dimensionality Reduction with PCA

# PCA

infidelity.pcadata <- infidelity %>% select_if(is.numeric)

infidelity.pca <- princomp(infidelity.pcadata, cor = T)

summary(infidelity.pca, loadings = T)

    geom_point(size = 1) + xlab("PC1") + ylab("PC2") + scale_color_manual(values = c("black",

    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold")) +

Linear Classifier

# linear classifier code here

infidelity.glm <- glm(data = infidelity, faithful ~ age + rating + 
    yearsmarried + religiousness + education, family = "binomial")


faithful_prob <- predict(infidelity.glm, type = "response")

# class diag
class_diag(faithful_prob, truth = infidelity$faithful, positive = 1)
